# Mobile Observability Dashboard ‚Äî Project Context

## Stack
- React 19, TypeScript 6, Vite 8
- Tailwind CSS v4 (via `@tailwindcss/vite` plugin ‚Äî no `tailwind.config.js`)
- Recharts v3 for all charts
- React Router v7 (not yet wired; navigation is state-driven in `App.tsx`)

## Source Layout
```
src/
  App.tsx           # Root: ThemeContext provider + section state + keyboard nav
  context/          # ThemeContext (isDark + toggle)
  lib/
    firebase.ts     # Firebase app init + Firestore export (reads VITE_FIREBASE_* env vars)
    datadog.ts      # Datadog Metrics API fetch wrapper (reads VITE_DATADOG_* env vars)
  hooks/
    useDarkMode.ts
    useChartColors.ts
    useFirestore.ts           # Generic useDocument<T> / useCollection<T> with onSnapshot
    useEngineeringData.ts     # Domain hook ‚Äî Engineering dashboard
    useSecurityData.ts        # Domain hook ‚Äî Security dashboard
    useSREData.ts             # Domain hook ‚Äî SRE dashboard
    useProductData.ts         # Domain hook ‚Äî Product dashboard
    useExecutiveData.ts       # Domain hook ‚Äî Executive dashboard
    useDatadogMetrics.ts      # Queries Datadog API ‚Üí writes to Firestore on interval
  pages/            # One file per persona dashboard (SRE, Engineering, Product, Security, Executive)
  components/
    layout/         # Sidebar, Topbar, Layout
    charts/         # ChartTooltip (shared tooltip component)
  data/             # mockData.ts ‚Äî fallback/reference mock data
  types/            # Shared TypeScript interfaces (Metric, Session, Crash, etc.)
  index.css         # All CSS custom properties and utility classes
```

## Navigation
Sections are `'sre' | 'engineering' | 'product' | 'security' | 'executive'` (type `Section` in `App.tsx`).  
Switch via `setSection` prop or keyboard shortcuts `1‚Äì5`.

## Firebase / Firestore Integration
Engineering and Security dashboards are wired to live Firestore real-time subscriptions.

**Config** ‚Äî create `.env.local` at the project root (never commit):
```
VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=
VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=
VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=
VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID=
```

**Data layer pattern:**
1. `src/lib/firebase.ts` ‚Äî initializes Firebase once, exports `db` and `isConfigured`
2. `src/hooks/useFirestore.ts` ‚Äî `useDocument<T>(path)` and `useCollection<T>(path, orderByField?)`, both returning `{ data, loading, error }`
3. Domain hooks compose the generic hooks and provide typed fallback mock data when Firebase is unconfigured or loading

**Firestore schema** (Engineering):
- `analytics/crashes/kpis/current` ‚Äî `{ crashFree, anrFree, affectedUsers, newSignatures }`
- `analytics/crashes/signatures` ‚Äî collection ordered by `order` field
- `analytics/crashes/versions` ‚Äî collection ordered by `order` field
- `analytics/crashes/trend` ‚Äî collection ordered by `order` field

**Firestore schema** (Security):
- `analytics/security/kpis/current` ‚Äî `{ mfaFatigue, geoImpossibilities, integrityViolations, accountsLocked, activeInvestigations }`
- `analytics/security/threats` ‚Äî collection ordered by `order` field
- `analytics/security/integrity` ‚Äî collection ordered by `order` field (stores `colorToken: 'warning'|'danger'`, resolved to CSS var by `resolveColor()`)
- `analytics/security/events` ‚Äî collection ordered by `order` field

**Firestore schema** (SRE):
- `analytics/sre/kpis/current` ‚Äî `{ crashFree, apiAvail, pushDelivery, timeToCode }`
- `analytics/sre/latency` ‚Äî collection ordered by `order` field: `{ time, p50, p95, p99 }`
- `analytics/sre/burn` ‚Äî collection ordered by `order` field: `{ label, width, value, colorToken }`
- `analytics/sre/deps` ‚Äî collection ordered by `order` field: `{ name, status, label, value }`
- `analytics/sre/alerts` ‚Äî collection ordered by `order` field: `{ badge, badgeLabel, text, age, action }`

**Firestore schema** (Product):
- `analytics/product/kpis/current` ‚Äî `{ mau, dau, stickiness, d30Retention }`
- `analytics/product/mauTrend` ‚Äî collection ordered by `order` field: `{ day, mau }`
- `analytics/product/funnel` ‚Äî collection ordered by `order` field: `{ label, pct, count, drop, dropColorToken }`
- `analytics/product/featureAdoption` ‚Äî collection ordered by `order` field: `{ label, pct }`
- `analytics/product/authMix` ‚Äî collection ordered by `order` field: `{ name, value }`

**Firestore schema** (Executive):
- `analytics/executive/kpis/current` ‚Äî `{ mau, installs, d30Retention, nps, rating }`
- `analytics/executive/mauGrowth` ‚Äî collection ordered by `order` field: `{ month, mau }`
- `analytics/executive/reliability` ‚Äî collection ordered by `order` field: `{ label, value, colorToken? }`
- `analytics/executive/security` ‚Äî collection ordered by `order` field: `{ label, value, colorToken? }`
- `analytics/executive/platformMix` ‚Äî collection ordered by `order` field: `{ label, pct, colorToken }`
- `analytics/executive/regions` ‚Äî collection ordered by `order` field: `{ label, value }`
- `analytics/executive/unitEcon` ‚Äî collection ordered by `order` field: `{ label, value, colorToken? }`

**When Firebase is not configured** ‚Äî dashboards display built-in mock values; no error is thrown. The console emits one warning.

## Datadog Integration
`useDatadogMetrics()` is mounted once in `App.tsx`. It queries Datadog on mount and every 60s, writing results into Firestore so all domain hooks pick up live values automatically.

**Config** ‚Äî add to `.env.local` (never commit):
```
VITE_DATADOG_API_KEY=
VITE_DATADOG_APP_KEY=
VITE_DATADOG_SITE=datadoghq.com   # or datadoghq.eu, us3.datadoghq.com, etc.
```

**Files:**
- `src/lib/datadog.ts` ‚Äî fetch wrapper for Datadog Metrics Query API v1 (`queryMetrics`, `latestValue`, `hoursAgo`, `daysAgo`)
- `src/hooks/useDatadogMetrics.ts` ‚Äî `METRIC_MAPPINGS` array maps Datadog query strings to Firestore doc paths + fields. Edit this array to add/change metrics. No-op when either Datadog or Firebase is unconfigured.

## Mock Data
All 5 dashboards have typed fallback mock data in their domain hooks. Displayed when Firebase is unconfigured or still loading.
